35/* register definitions according to the TFP410 data sheet */
36#define TFP410_VID 0x014C
37#define TFP410_DID 0x0410
38
39#define TFP410_VID_LO 0x00
40#define TFP410_VID_HI 0x01
41#define TFP410_DID_LO 0x02
42#define TFP410_DID_HI 0x03
43#define TFP410_REV 0x04
44
45#define TFP410_CTL_1 0x08
46#define TFP410_CTL_1_TDIS (1<<6)
47#define TFP410_CTL_1_VEN (1<<5)
48#define TFP410_CTL_1_HEN (1<<4)
49#define TFP410_CTL_1_DSEL (1<<3)
50#define TFP410_CTL_1_BSEL (1<<2)
51#define TFP410_CTL_1_EDGE (1<<1)
52#define TFP410_CTL_1_PD (1<<0)
53
54#define TFP410_CTL_2 0x09
55#define TFP410_CTL_2_VLOW (1<<7)
56#define TFP410_CTL_2_MSEL_MASK (0x7<<4)
57#define TFP410_CTL_2_MSEL (1<<4)
58#define TFP410_CTL_2_TSEL (1<<3)
59#define TFP410_CTL_2_RSEN (1<<2)
60#define TFP410_CTL_2_HTPLG (1<<1)
61#define TFP410_CTL_2_MDI (1<<0)
62
63#define TFP410_CTL_3 0x0A
64#define TFP410_CTL_3_DK_MASK (0x7<<5)
65#define TFP410_CTL_3_DK (1<<5)
66#define TFP410_CTL_3_DKEN (1<<4)
67#define TFP410_CTL_3_CTL_MASK (0x7<<1)
68#define TFP410_CTL_3_CTL (1<<1)
69
70#define TFP410_USERCFG 0x0B
71
72#define TFP410_DE_DLY 0x32
73
74#define TFP410_DE_CTL 0x33
75#define TFP410_DE_CTL_DEGEN (1<<6)
76#define TFP410_DE_CTL_VSPOL (1<<5)
77#define TFP410_DE_CTL_HSPOL (1<<4)
78#define TFP410_DE_CTL_DEDLY8 (1<<0)
79
80#define TFP410_DE_TOP 0x34
81
82#define TFP410_DE_CNT_LO 0x36
83#define TFP410_DE_CNT_HI 0x37
84
85#define TFP410_DE_LIN_LO 0x38
86#define TFP410_DE_LIN_HI 0x39
87
88#define TFP410_H_RES_LO 0x3A
89#define TFP410_H_RES_HI 0x3B
90
91#define TFP410_V_RES_LO 0x3C
92#define TFP410_V_RES_HI 0x3D
93
94struct tfp410_priv {
95 bool quiet;
96};
97
98static bool tfp410_readb(struct intel_dvo_device *dvo, int addr, uint8_t *ch)
99{
100 struct tfp410_priv *tfp = dvo->dev_priv;
101 struct i2c_adapter *adapter = dvo->i2c_bus;
102 u8 out_buf[2];
103 u8 in_buf[2];
104
105 struct i2c_msg msgs[] = {
106 {
107 .addr = dvo->slave_addr,
108 .flags = 0,
109 .len = 1,
110 .buf = out_buf,
111 },
112 {
113 .addr = dvo->slave_addr,
114 .flags = I2C_M_RD,
115 .len = 1,
116 .buf = in_buf,
117 }
118 };
119
120 out_buf[0] = addr;
121 out_buf[1] = 0;
122
123 if (i2c_transfer(adapter, msgs, 2) == 2) {
124 *ch = in_buf[0];
125 return true;
126 }
127
128 if (!tfp->quiet) {
129 DRM_DEBUG_KMS("Unable to read register 0x%02x from %s:%02x.\n",
130 addr, adapter->name, dvo->slave_addr);
131 }
132 return false;
133}
134
135static bool tfp410_writeb(struct intel_dvo_device *dvo, int addr, uint8_t ch)
136{
137 struct tfp410_priv *tfp = dvo->dev_priv;
138 struct i2c_adapter *adapter = dvo->i2c_bus;
139 uint8_t out_buf[2];
140 struct i2c_msg msg = {
141 .addr = dvo->slave_addr,
142 .flags = 0,
143 .len = 2,
144 .buf = out_buf,
145 };
146
147 out_buf[0] = addr;
148 out_buf[1] = ch;
149
150 if (i2c_transfer(adapter, &msg, 1) == 1)
151 return true;
152
153 if (!tfp->quiet) {
154 DRM_DEBUG_KMS("Unable to write register 0x%02x to %s:%d.\n",
155 addr, adapter->name, dvo->slave_addr);
156 }
157
158 return false;
159}
160
161static int tfp410_getid(struct intel_dvo_device *dvo, int addr)
162{
163 uint8_t ch1, ch2;
164
165 if (tfp410_readb(dvo, addr+0, &ch1) &&
166 tfp410_readb(dvo, addr+1, &ch2))
167 return ((ch2 << 8) & 0xFF00) | (ch1 & 0x00FF);
168
169 return -1;
170}
171
172/* Ti TFP410 driver for chip on i2c bus */
173static bool tfp410_init(struct intel_dvo_device *dvo,
174 struct i2c_adapter *adapter)
175{
176 /* this will detect the tfp410 chip on the specified i2c bus */
177 struct tfp410_priv *tfp;
178 int id;
179
180 tfp = kzalloc(sizeof(struct tfp410_priv), GFP_KERNEL);
181 if (tfp == NULL)
182 return false;
183
184 dvo->i2c_bus = adapter;
185 dvo->dev_priv = tfp;
186 tfp->quiet = true;
187
188 if ((id = tfp410_getid(dvo, TFP410_VID_LO)) != TFP410_VID) {
189 DRM_DEBUG_KMS("tfp410 not detected got VID %X: from %s "
190 "Slave %d.\n",
191 id, adapter->name, dvo->slave_addr);
192 goto out;
193 }
194
195 if ((id = tfp410_getid(dvo, TFP410_DID_LO)) != TFP410_DID) {
196 DRM_DEBUG_KMS("tfp410 not detected got DID %X: from %s "
197 "Slave %d.\n",
198 id, adapter->name, dvo->slave_addr);
199 goto out;
200 }
201 tfp->quiet = false;
202 return true;
203out:
204 kfree(tfp);
205 return false;
206}
207
208static enum drm_connector_status tfp410_detect(struct intel_dvo_device *dvo)
209{
210 enum drm_connector_status ret = connector_status_disconnected;
211 uint8_t ctl2;
212
213 if (tfp410_readb(dvo, TFP410_CTL_2, &ctl2)) {
214 if (ctl2 & TFP410_CTL_2_RSEN)
215 ret = connector_status_connected;
216 else
217 ret = connector_status_disconnected;
218 }
219
220 return ret;
221}
222
223static enum drm_mode_status tfp410_mode_valid(struct intel_dvo_device *dvo,
224 struct drm_display_mode *mode)
225{
226 return MODE_OK;
227}
228
229static void tfp410_mode_set(struct intel_dvo_device *dvo,
230 const struct drm_display_mode *mode,
231 const struct drm_display_mode *adjusted_mode)
232{
233 /* As long as the basics are set up, since we don't have clock dependencies
234 * in the mode setup, we can just leave the registers alone and everything
235 * will work fine.
236 */
237 /* don't do much */
238 return;
239}
240
241/* set the tfp410 power state */
242static void tfp410_dpms(struct intel_dvo_device *dvo, bool enable)
243{
244 uint8_t ctl1;
245
246 if (!tfp410_readb(dvo, TFP410_CTL_1, &ctl1))
247 return;
248
249 if (enable)
250 ctl1 |= TFP410_CTL_1_PD;
251 else
252 ctl1 &= ~TFP410_CTL_1_PD;
253
254 tfp410_writeb(dvo, TFP410_CTL_1, ctl1);
255}
256
257static bool tfp410_get_hw_state(struct intel_dvo_device *dvo)
258{
259 uint8_t ctl1;
260
261 if (!tfp410_readb(dvo, TFP410_CTL_1, &ctl1))
262 return false;
263
264 if (ctl1 & TFP410_CTL_1_PD)
265 return true;
266 else
267 return false;
268}
269
270static void tfp410_dump_regs(struct intel_dvo_device *dvo)
271{
272 uint8_t val, val2;
273
274 tfp410_readb(dvo, TFP410_REV, &val);
275 DRM_DEBUG_KMS("TFP410_REV: 0x%02X\n", val);
276 tfp410_readb(dvo, TFP410_CTL_1, &val);
277 DRM_DEBUG_KMS("TFP410_CTL1: 0x%02X\n", val);
278 tfp410_readb(dvo, TFP410_CTL_2, &val);
279 DRM_DEBUG_KMS("TFP410_CTL2: 0x%02X\n", val);
280 tfp410_readb(dvo, TFP410_CTL_3, &val);
281 DRM_DEBUG_KMS("TFP410_CTL3: 0x%02X\n", val);
282 tfp410_readb(dvo, TFP410_USERCFG, &val);
283 DRM_DEBUG_KMS("TFP410_USERCFG: 0x%02X\n", val);
284 tfp410_readb(dvo, TFP410_DE_DLY, &val);
285 DRM_DEBUG_KMS("TFP410_DE_DLY: 0x%02X\n", val);
286 tfp410_readb(dvo, TFP410_DE_CTL, &val);
287 DRM_DEBUG_KMS("TFP410_DE_CTL: 0x%02X\n", val);
288 tfp410_readb(dvo, TFP410_DE_TOP, &val);
289 DRM_DEBUG_KMS("TFP410_DE_TOP: 0x%02X\n", val);
290 tfp410_readb(dvo, TFP410_DE_CNT_LO, &val);
291 tfp410_readb(dvo, TFP410_DE_CNT_HI, &val2);
292 DRM_DEBUG_KMS("TFP410_DE_CNT: 0x%02X%02X\n", val2, val);
293 tfp410_readb(dvo, TFP410_DE_LIN_LO, &val);
294 tfp410_readb(dvo, TFP410_DE_LIN_HI, &val2);
295 DRM_DEBUG_KMS("TFP410_DE_LIN: 0x%02X%02X\n", val2, val);
296 tfp410_readb(dvo, TFP410_H_RES_LO, &val);
297 tfp410_readb(dvo, TFP410_H_RES_HI, &val2);
298 DRM_DEBUG_KMS("TFP410_H_RES: 0x%02X%02X\n", val2, val);
299 tfp410_readb(dvo, TFP410_V_RES_LO, &val);
300 tfp410_readb(dvo, TFP410_V_RES_HI, &val2);
301 DRM_DEBUG_KMS("TFP410_V_RES: 0x%02X%02X\n", val2, val);
302}
303
304static void tfp410_destroy(struct intel_dvo_device *dvo)
305{
306 struct tfp410_priv *tfp = dvo->dev_priv;
307
308 if (tfp) {
309 kfree(tfp);
310 dvo->dev_priv = NULL;
311 }
312}
313
314struct intel_dvo_dev_ops tfp410_ops = {
315 .init = tfp410_init,
316 .detect = tfp410_detect,
317 .mode_valid = tfp410_mode_valid,
318 .mode_set = tfp410_mode_set,
319 .dpms = tfp410_dpms,
320 .get_hw_state = tfp410_get_hw_state,
321 .dump_regs = tfp410_dump_regs,
322 .destroy = tfp410_destroy,
323};
